Qualifier: Enter uncertainty about the identification (aff., cf., ?, etc.). This applies to the lowest taxonomic level.
Species: In lower case. Can enter "sp." if Indeterminate.
Species Author: Will be automatically populated by herbarium staff based on currently accepted names. Can leave blank unless you have special notes.
Subspecies: In lower case. Name only, do not enter "ssp." or "subsp." before name.
Subspecies Author: Will be automatically populated by herbarium staff based on currently accepted names. Can leave blank unless you have special notes.
Variety: In lower case. Name only, do not enter "var." before name.
Variety Author: Will be automatically populated by herbarium staff based on currently accepted names. Can leave blank unless you have special notes.
Forma: In lower case. Name only, do not enter "f." before name.
Forma Author: Will be automatically populated by herbarium staff based on currently accepted names. Can leave blank unless you have special notes.
Cultivar: In single quotations. First letter is uppercase.
Location:
Try to go from larger to smaller, such as: 
County, Regional District, City, Town, Street, Corner, etc. 
Expand abbreviations (e.g. Rd. to Road, Mtn. to Mountain, N to north, etc.). Unless the first word is a proper noun, begin field with a lower case letter. Please separate with commas. Do not end with a period.
VLatDegree: For all latitude and longitude coordinates, please enter the numbers only with no symbols or hemispheres, & standardize # of digits
UTM:
Please follow the format 
"zone easting northing" 
(i.e. 11U 500988 5683607)
Grid Reference:
Please be as specific 
as possible (TRSec, etc.)
VDatum:
Enter the datum here 
(i.e. NAD27, NAD83, WGS84)
VCoordinateUncertainty: Enter the coordinate uncertainty here (in m or ft), with a space between the number and the unit.
Habitat:
Be as specific as possible, and please include 
associated species in this section (use full names for genera, not abbreviations). First letter is always uppercase. Can use semi-colons to separate sentences if needed. Do not end with a period.
Altitude:
Please follow the value 
by a space and 'm' or 'ft' 
(as applicable & with no punctuation). The following may be included: ca. and approx.. Change ~ to approx. and approximately to approx.
Date Collected: Please format exactly as shown with no commas (YYYY MMM DD). Always enter DD as two digits.
Primary Collector: Only one collector should be listed (Primary collector); Include both first and last name,  middle initial optional.
Other Collectors: This is where the other collectors go. Separate names by a comma only. Include both first and last names, middle initial optional.
Collector Number: Collection #: A unique number given by the collector to identify the specimen.
Determined By:
Determiner name(s). 
Please separate names 
by a comma only. Include both first and last names, middle initial optional.
Field Notes: Anything important to add about collected specimen (i.e. abundance, flower colour, height, plot number, etc.) Please put associated species in the habitat field. Unless the first word is a proper noun, begin field with a lower case letter. Sentences can be separated with a semi-colon; do not end with a period.
Original Herbarium: If the specimen was originally housed at a herbarium other than UBC Herbarium
Citations: Include the reference for any publication in which this specimen is cited.
Genbank:
Input corresponding research number.
 Separate by a comma only.
BOLD Number:
Input corresponding research number.
Separate by a comma only.
Georeference Notes: Leave any georeferencing notes in this column including end range coordinates, geolocation name changes and other extra information
